@startuml TortillaCloud_Architecture
title Tortilla Cloud - Current Structure (from repo)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

component "Spring MVC" as MVC
component "Spring Security" as Security
component "Spring Data JPA" as JPA
database "H2 DB (runtime)" as H2

package "src/main/java/com/Tortilla_cloud/controller" as controllers {
  component "HomeController" as HomeController <<Controller>>
  component "DesignTortillaController" as DesignTortillaController <<Controller>>
  component "OrdersCurrentController" as OrdersCurrentController <<Controller>>
}

package "src/main/java/com/Tortilla_cloud/security" as security_pkg {
  component "SecurityConfig" as SecurityConfig <<Configuration>>
}

package "src/main/java/com/Tortilla_cloud/model" as models {
  component "Ingredient" as Ingredient <<Entity>>
  component "Type" as Type <<Enum>>
  component "Tortilla" as Tortilla <<Entity>>
  component "Order" as Order <<Entity>>
}

package "src/main/java/com/Tortilla_cloud/repository" as repos {
  interface "IngredientRepository" as IngredientRepository <<CrudRepository>>
  interface "TortillaRepository" as TortillaRepository <<CrudRepository>>
  interface "OrderRepository" as OrderRepository <<CrudRepository>>
}

package "src/main/resources/templates (Thymeleaf)" as views {
  artifact "home.html" as home_html
  artifact "login.html" as login_html
  artifact "design.html" as design_html
  artifact "orderForm.html" as orderForm_html
}

package "src/main/resources/static" as static {
  folder "images/" as images
  artifact "tortilla1.jpg"
  artifact "tortilla2.jpg"
  artifact "parotta.png"
}

Security -down-> MVC : filter chain\n(authn/authz)
Security ..> SecurityConfig
MVC -down-> controllers
controllers ..> views : returns view name
controllers ..> models : binds + validates

JPA -down-> repos
repos ..> models : persists
JPA --> H2

home_html ..> images
login_html ..> Security : POST /login (handled by Spring Security)
home_html ..> Security : POST /logout (CSRF)
design_html ..> controllers : POST /design
orderForm_html ..> controllers : POST /orders

Tortilla ..> Ingredient : ManyToMany
Order ..> Tortilla : ManyToMany

note right of DesignTortillaController
Today: ingredients are hard-coded (in-memory list).
Repositories exist but are not wired into controllers yet.
end note

note right of SecurityConfig
Form login enabled:
- GET /login -> HomeController returns login.html
- POST /login handled by Spring Security
- /design and /orders/** require authentication
end note

@enduml

@startuml TortillaCloud_Domain_Model
title Tortilla Cloud - Domain Model (from repo)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class Ingredient <<Entity>>
enum Type
class Tortilla <<Entity>>
class Order <<Entity>>

Tortilla "*" -- "*" Ingredient : ingredients\n@ManyToMany (unidirectional)
Order "*" -- "*" Tortilla : tortillas\n@ManyToMany (unidirectional)

@enduml

@startuml TortillaCloud_Current_Flow
title Tortilla Cloud - Current Request Flow

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #ffffff
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #1f1f1f
  LifeLineBorderColor #9a9a9a
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #ffffff
  ParticipantBorderColor #9a9aa8
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #e9e9f2
  ParticipantFontColor #111111
  ActorBorderColor #6b6b6b
  ActorBackgroundColor #ffffff
  NoteBorderColor #b59b52
  NoteBackgroundColor #fff2cc
  DividerBorderColor #1f1f1f
  DividerBackgroundColor #ffffff
}

actor Customer
participant Browser
participant "Spring Security\n(FilterChain)" as Security
participant HomeController
participant DesignTortillaController
participant OrdersCurrentController

participant "Sample Ingredient List" as IngredientList
participant "Type enum" as TypeEnum

participant "Thymeleaf home.html" as home_html
participant "Thymeleaf login.html" as login_html
participant "Thymeleaf design.html" as design_html
participant "Thymeleaf orderForm.html" as orderForm_html

database "Database" as DB
participant AuthController
participant CartController
participant CheckoutController
participant PaymentController
participant "Payment Gateway" as Gateway

== Home Page ==
Customer -> Browser : Open application
Browser -> Security : GET /
Security -> HomeController : Allowed (permitAll)
HomeController -> home_html : return "home"
home_html --> Browser : Render homepage
Browser --> Customer : Show landing page

== Login (Security) ==
note right of Security
Form login configured:
- GET /login renders a custom template
- POST /login handled by Spring Security
- On success, redirect -> /design
- On failure, redirect -> /login?error
Logout:
- POST /logout (CSRF protected)
- Redirect -> /login?logout
end note

== Design Page ==
Customer -> Browser : Open /design
Browser -> Security : GET /design
alt Not authenticated
  Security --> Browser : 302 Redirect -> /login
  Browser -> Security : GET /login
  Security -> HomeController : Allowed (permitAll)
  HomeController -> login_html : return "login"
  login_html --> Browser : Render login page
  Browser --> Customer : Show login form

  Customer -> Browser : Submit credentials
  Browser -> Security : POST /login (username, password, _csrf)
  alt Invalid credentials
    Security --> Browser : 302 Redirect -> /login?error
    Browser -> Security : GET /login?error
    Security -> HomeController : Allowed (permitAll)
    HomeController -> login_html : return "login"
    login_html --> Browser : Render error message
  else Valid credentials
    Security --> Browser : 302 Redirect -> /design
    Browser -> Security : GET /design
  end
end

Security -> DesignTortillaController : Allowed (authenticated)
DesignTortillaController -> IngredientList : getIngredients()
IngredientList --> DesignTortillaController : ingredients
DesignTortillaController -> TypeEnum : read enum values
TypeEnum --> DesignTortillaController : types

note right of DesignTortillaController
Adds model attributes:
- wrap / protein / veggies / cheese / sauce (lists)
- design (form backing)
end note

DesignTortillaController -> design_html : return "design" with model
design_html --> Browser : Render design page
Browser --> Customer : Show design page

Customer -> Browser : Submit tortilla design
Browser -> Security : POST /design (Tortilla, _csrf)
Security -> DesignTortillaController : Allowed (authenticated)
alt Validation errors
  DesignTortillaController -> design_html : return "design" with errors
  design_html --> Browser : Render errors
else Valid
  DesignTortillaController --> Browser : Redirect -> /orders/current
end

== Order Page ==
Browser -> Security : GET /orders/current
Security -> OrdersCurrentController : Allowed (authenticated)
OrdersCurrentController -> orderForm_html : return "orderForm"
orderForm_html --> Browser : Render order form

Customer -> Browser : Submit order
Browser -> Security : POST /orders (Order, _csrf)
Security -> OrdersCurrentController : Allowed (authenticated)
alt Validation errors
  OrdersCurrentController -> orderForm_html : return "orderForm" with errors
  orderForm_html --> Browser : Render errors
else Valid
  OrdersCurrentController --> Browser : Redirect -> /
end

== Logout ==
Customer -> Browser : Click Logout
Browser -> Security : POST /logout (_csrf)
Security --> Browser : 302 Redirect -> /login?logout
Browser -> Security : GET /login?logout
Security -> HomeController : Allowed (permitAll)
HomeController -> login_html : return "login"
login_html --> Browser : Render logout message

note left of Browser
Current state:
- Server-rendered Spring MVC app
- Thymeleaf templates for UI
- Ingredients are hard-coded (in-memory list)
- JPA + H2 are configured, but controllers don't persist orders/designs yet
- Spring Security form login is enabled with a custom /login page
end note

== Future Additions ==
Browser -> DesignTortillaController : GET /design
DesignTortillaController -> DB : load ingredients
DB --> DesignTortillaController : ingredients
DesignTortillaController -> design_html : return "design"

Browser -> CartController : POST /cart
CartController -> DB : validate item / update cart
DB --> CartController : updated cart state

Browser -> AuthController : POST /register / login
AuthController -> DB : validate user / create session
DB --> AuthController : user/session data

Browser -> CheckoutController : POST /checkout
CheckoutController -> DB : save order
DB --> CheckoutController : order id / status
CheckoutController -> PaymentController : initiate payment
PaymentController -> Gateway : process payment
Gateway --> PaymentController : payment status
PaymentController --> Browser : payment result

note left of Browser
Recommended next steps:
- Add services (IngredientService, OrderService)
- Wire repositories + persistence (JPA)
- Add real users (UserDetailsService + password encoding) instead of generated dev password
- Add cart + checkout controllers
- Integrate a payment gateway
end note

@enduml

@startuml TortillaCloud_Future_Flow
title Tortilla Cloud - Future Flow (after persistence + real users + cart + payment gateway)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #111009
  BorderColor #3a3326
  FontColor #e9e2d4
}

start
:GET / (Home);
:Browse menu / featured items;

if (Authenticated?) then (yes)
  :Continue as logged-in user;
else (no)
  :Register / Login;
endif

:Add items to Cart;
:View Cart (/cart);
:Edit quantities / remove items;

if (Has saved address?) then (yes)
  :Select address;
else (no)
  :Add delivery address;
endif

:Checkout (/checkout);
:Apply coupon / offer (optional);
:Choose delivery slot (optional);

:Select payment method;
if (Online payment?) then (yes)
  :Create PaymentIntent / Order draft;
  :Redirect to Payment Gateway (Stripe/Razorpay/PayPal);
  :Gateway callback + webhook verification;
  if (Payment succeeded?) then (yes)
    :Confirm order;
  else (no)
    :Show payment failed + retry;
  endif
else (Cash on delivery)
  :Confirm order (cash on delivery);
endif

:Order confirmation page;
:Send notifications (email/SMS/WhatsApp);
:Order tracking (optional);
:Order history (/account/orders);
stop

note right
Suggested next additions beyond login/cart/payments:
- Admin dashboard (manage menu, pricing, availability)
- Inventory + ingredient availability gating
- Reviews/ratings
- Delivery partner assignment + status updates
- Refunds + cancellations + payment reconciliation
- Observability: audit logs, metrics, error tracking
end note

@enduml
